#!/bin/bash


if [ "$#" -ne 3 ]; then echo "Usage: ./install <openrc> <tag> <key>"; exit 1; fi
source "$1"
TAG="$2"
PRIVATE_KEY="$3"
PUBLIC_KEY="${PRIVATE_KEY}.pub"

chmod 600 "$PRIVATE_KEY"
rm -f .temp_known_hosts

EXT_NET=$(openstack network list --external -f value -c ID | head -n 1)

NUM_NODES=$(grep -i "^service_nodes" servers.conf | awk -F "=" '{print $2}' | tr -d '\r ' || echo "3")
if [ -z "$NUM_NODES" ]; then NUM_NODES=3; fi

IMAGE_ID=$(openstack image list -f value | grep -i "Ubuntu" | awk '{print $1}' | head -n 1)
FLAVOR_SMALL=$(openstack flavor list -f value -c Name | grep -i "small" | head -1)
FLAVOR_TINY=$(openstack flavor list -f value -c Name | grep -i "tiny" | head -1)

echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Starting deployment of $TAG"
echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Node count: $NUM_NODES"

# ---- NETWORK ----
if ! openstack network show ${TAG}_network &>/dev/null; then
    echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Creating network..."
    NET_ID=$(openstack network create "${TAG}_network" -f value -c id)
    openstack subnet create --network "$NET_ID" \
        --subnet-range 192.168.1.0/24 \
        --dns-nameserver 8.8.8.8 \
        --dns-nameserver 1.1.1.1 \
        "${TAG}_subnet" > /dev/null
else
    NET_ID=$(openstack network show ${TAG}_network -f value -c id)
fi

# ---- ROUTER ----
if ! openstack router show ${TAG}_router &>/dev/null; then
    echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Creating router..."
    openstack router create "${TAG}_router" > /dev/null
    openstack router add subnet "${TAG}_router" "${TAG}_subnet"
    openstack router set --external-gateway "$EXT_NET" "${TAG}_router"
fi

# ---- SECURITY GROUP ----
if ! openstack security group show ${TAG}_sg &>/dev/null; then
    echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Creating security group..."
    openstack security group create "${TAG}_sg" > /dev/null
    openstack security group rule create --protocol tcp --dst-port 22 "${TAG}_sg" > /dev/null
    openstack security group rule create --protocol tcp --dst-port 5000 "${TAG}_sg" > /dev/null
    openstack security group rule create --protocol udp --dst-port 6000 "${TAG}_sg" > /dev/null
    openstack security group rule create --protocol udp --dst-port 161 "${TAG}_sg" > /dev/null
    openstack security group rule create --protocol icmp "${TAG}_sg" > /dev/null
fi

# ---- KEYPAIR ----
if ! openstack keypair show ${TAG}_key &>/dev/null; then
    echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Creating keypair..."
    openstack keypair create --public-key "$PUBLIC_KEY" "${TAG}_key" > /dev/null
fi

# ---- FLOATING IPs ----
FIP1=$(openstack floating ip list --status DOWN -f value -c "Floating IP Address" | head -n 1 || true)
if [ -z "$FIP1" ]; then FIP1=$(openstack floating ip create "$EXT_NET" -f value -c floating_ip_address); fi

FIP2=$(openstack floating ip list --status DOWN -f value -c "Floating IP Address" | grep -v "$FIP1" | head -n 1 || true)
if [ -z "$FIP2" ]; then FIP2=$(openstack floating ip create "$EXT_NET" -f value -c floating_ip_address); fi

echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Bastion IP: $FIP1, Proxy IP: $FIP2"

# ---- SERVERS ----
if ! openstack server show ${TAG}_bastion &>/dev/null; then
    echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Launching ${TAG}_bastion..."
    openstack server create --flavor $FLAVOR_SMALL --image "$IMAGE_ID" \
        --network "$NET_ID" --security-group "${TAG}_sg" \
        --key-name "${TAG}_key" "${TAG}_bastion" > /dev/null
fi

if ! openstack server show ${TAG}_proxy &>/dev/null; then
    echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Launching ${TAG}_proxy..."
    openstack server create --flavor $FLAVOR_SMALL --image "$IMAGE_ID" \
        --network "$NET_ID" --security-group "${TAG}_sg" \
        --key-name "${TAG}_key" "${TAG}_proxy" > /dev/null
fi

for ((i = 1; i <= NUM_NODES; i++)); do
    if ! openstack server show ${TAG}_node${i} &>/dev/null; then
        echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Launching ${TAG}_node${i}..."
        openstack server create --flavor $FLAVOR_TINY --image "$IMAGE_ID" \
            --network "$NET_ID" --security-group "${TAG}_sg" \
            --key-name "${TAG}_key" "${TAG}_node${i}" > /dev/null
    fi
done

# ---- WAIT FOR ACTIVE ----
echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Waiting for all servers to become ACTIVE..."
for SERVER in ${TAG}_bastion ${TAG}_proxy $(seq 1 $NUM_NODES | xargs -I{} echo ${TAG}_node{}); do
    while true; do
        STATUS=$(openstack server show $SERVER -f value -c status 2>/dev/null)
        if [ "$STATUS" = "ACTIVE" ]; then echo -n "[$SERVER done]"; break; fi
        sleep 5
    done
done
echo ""

# ---- ATTACH FLOATING IPs ----
openstack server add floating ip ${TAG}_bastion $FIP1 2>/dev/null || true
openstack server add floating ip ${TAG}_proxy $FIP2 2>/dev/null || true
echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Floating IPs attached."

# ---- WAIT FOR BASTION SSH ----
echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Waiting for bastion SSH..."
RETRY=0
while [ $RETRY -lt 40 ]; do
    if ssh -o ConnectTimeout=5 -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no \
        -o UserKnownHostsFile=./.temp_known_hosts \
        -q -i "$PRIVATE_KEY" ubuntu@"$FIP1" 'exit'; then
        echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Bastion SSH ready!"
        break
    fi
    sleep 10
    RETRY=$((RETRY + 1))
done

# ---- GET NODE IPs ----
PROXY_IP=$(openstack server show ${TAG}_proxy -f value -c addresses | grep -oP '[\d.]+' | head -1)

# ---- GENERATE SSH CONFIG ----
SSH_CONFIG="${TAG}_SSHconfig"
cat > $SSH_CONFIG << SSHEOF
Host ${TAG}_bastion
    HostName $FIP1
    User ubuntu
    IdentityFile $PRIVATE_KEY
    StrictHostKeyChecking no
    UserKnownHostsFile ./.temp_known_hosts

Host ${TAG}_proxy
    HostName $PROXY_IP
    User ubuntu
    IdentityFile $PRIVATE_KEY
    StrictHostKeyChecking no
    UserKnownHostsFile ./.temp_known_hosts
    ProxyJump ${TAG}_bastion

SSHEOF

for i in $(seq 1 $NUM_NODES); do
    NODE_IP=$(openstack server show ${TAG}_node${i} -f value -c addresses | grep -oP '[\d.]+' | head -1)
    cat >> $SSH_CONFIG << SSHEOF
Host ${TAG}_node${i}
    HostName $NODE_IP
    User ubuntu
    IdentityFile $PRIVATE_KEY
    StrictHostKeyChecking no
    UserKnownHostsFile ./.temp_known_hosts
    ProxyJump ${TAG}_bastion

SSHEOF
done

echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') SSH config saved to $SSH_CONFIG"

# ---- GENERATE ANSIBLE HOSTS ----
cat > ansible/hosts << HOSTS
[bastion]
bastion ansible_host=$FIP1

[proxy]
proxy ansible_host=$PROXY_IP

[nodes]
HOSTS

for i in $(seq 1 $NUM_NODES); do
    NODE_IP=$(openstack server show ${TAG}_node${i} -f value -c addresses | grep -oP '[\d.]+' | head -1)
    echo "node${i} ansible_host=$NODE_IP" >> ansible/hosts
done

cat >> ansible/hosts << HOSTS

[all:vars]
ansible_user=ubuntu
ansible_ssh_private_key_file=$PRIVATE_KEY
ansible_ssh_common_args='-o ControlMaster=no -o ControlPath=none -o ConnectTimeout=60 -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o UserKnownHostsFile=./.temp_known_hosts -o ProxyCommand="ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o UserKnownHostsFile=./.temp_known_hosts -W %h:%p -q -i $PRIVATE_KEY ubuntu@$FIP1"'
HOSTS

echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Running Ansible playbook..."
export ANSIBLE_HOST_KEY_CHECKING=False
export ANSIBLE_TIMEOUT=60
ANSIBLE_SSH_RETRIES=5 ansible-playbook -i ansible/hosts ansible/site.yml

# ---- VALIDATE ----
echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Validating deployment..."
for i in 1 2 3; do
    RESPONSE=$(curl -s http://$FIP2:5000)
    echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Request$i: $RESPONSE"
done

echo "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') Deployment complete! Bastion: $FIP1 Proxy: $FIP2"
